<section xml:id="C28.S26">
<title>Asymptotic Approximations for Large <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S26.m1">q</Math></title>         
  
<subsection xml:id="C28.S26.SS1">
<title>Goldstein’s Expansions</title>        
 
<para xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p1.s1">
Denote <Math equation-number="28.26.1" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S26.E1">{\mathrm{Mc}^{(3)}_{m}}\left(z,h\right)=\dfrac{e^{\mathrm{i}\phi}}{(\pi h\cosh z )^{\ifrac{1}{2}}}\*\left(\mathrm{Fc}_{m}\left(z,h\right)-\mathrm{i}\mathrm{Gc} _{m}\left(z,h\right)\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.26.2" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S26.E2">\mathrm{i}{\mathrm{Ms}^{(3)}_{m+1}}\left(z,h\right)=\dfrac{e^{\mathrm{i}\phi}} {(\pi h\cosh z)^{\ifrac{1}{2}}}\*{\left(\mathrm{Fs}_{m}\left(z,h\right)- \mathrm{i}\mathrm{Gs}_{m}\left(z,h\right)\right)},</Math> where <Math equation-number="28.26.3" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S26.E3">\phi=2h\sinh z-\left(m+\tfrac{1}{2}\right)\operatorname{arctan}\left(\sinh z \right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p1.s2">
Then as <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p1.m1">h\to+\infty</Math> with fixed <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p1.m2">z</Math> in <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p1.m3">\Re z&gt;0</Math> and fixed <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p1.m4">s=2m+1</Math> ,
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p2.s1">
 <Math equation-number="28.26.4" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S26.E4">\mathrm{Fc}_{m}\left(z,h\right)\sim 1+\dfrac{s}{8h{\cosh^{2}}z}+\dfrac{1}{2^{1 1}h^{2}}\left(\dfrac{s^{4}+86s^{2}+105}{{\cosh^{4}}z}-\dfrac{s^{4}+22s^{2}+57} {{\cosh^{2}}z}\right)+\dfrac{1}{2^{14}h^{3}}\left(-\dfrac{s^{5}+14s^{3}+33s}{{ \cosh^{2}}z}-\dfrac{2s^{5}+124s^{3}+1122s}{{\cosh^{4}}z}+\dfrac{3s^{5}+290s^{3 }+1627s}{{\cosh^{6}}z}\right)+\cdots,</Math> <Math equation-number="28.26.5" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S26.E5">\mathrm{Gc}_{m}\left(z,h\right)\sim\dfrac{\sinh z}{{\cosh^{2}}z}\left(\dfrac{s ^{2}+3}{2^{5}h}+\dfrac{1}{2^{9}h^{2}}\left(s^{3}+3s+\dfrac{4s^{3}+44s}{{\cosh^ {2}}z}\right)+\dfrac{1}{2^{14}h^{3}}\left(5s^{4}+34s^{2}+9-\dfrac{s^{6}-47s^{4 }+667s^{2}+2835}{12{\cosh^{2}}z}+\dfrac{s^{6}+505s^{4}+12139s^{2}+10395}{12{ \cosh^{4}}z}\right)\right)+\cdots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p3.s1">
The asymptotic expansions of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p3.m1">\mathrm{Fs}_{m}\left(z,h\right)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p3.m2">\mathrm{Gs}_{m}\left(z,h\right)</Math> in the same circumstances are also given by the right-hand sides of (28.26.4) and (28.26.5), respectively.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p4">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C28.S26.SS1.p4.s1">
For additional terms see Goldstein (1927).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
